## 2. Arity-6 Event Encoding (agent, action, patient, time, location, instrument)

Arity 6 → tree depth 3. Recall budget from R1: J_signal = 1/(n-1) = 1/5 = **0.20 raw**, post-cleanup recall **~0.74** (under the J_a=0.85 retrieval model). Below the comfortable line but above 0.5 — exactly what arity-6 should be.

### Encoding formula

```
T_event = shift(AGENT,     p[agent])
        ⊕ shift(ACTION,    p[action])
        ⊕ shift(PATIENT,   p[patient])
        ⊕ shift(TIME,      p[time])
        ⊕ shift(LOCATION,  p[location])
        ⊕ shift(INSTRUMENT,p[instrument])
```

where `p[role]` are the 6 distinct path-shifts (leaves of a depth-3 tree).

### Query formula per role (recover PATIENT given the other 5)

```
P̂ = shift⁻¹( T ⊕ shift(AGENT,…) ⊕ shift(ACTION,…)
               ⊕ shift(TIME,…) ⊕ shift(LOCATION,…)
               ⊕ shift(INSTRUMENT,…),  p[patient] )
   → AtomMemory.cleanup(P̂)
```

```rust
pub struct EventCodec {
    binder: HierBinder,
    paths: [Vec<u8>; 6], // agent,action,patient,time,location,instrument
}

impl EventCodec {
    pub fn new() -> Self {
        // 6 leaves on a depth-3 binary tree (8 slots, use first 6).
        let paths = [
            vec![0,0,0], vec![0,0,1], vec![0,1,0],
            vec![0,1,1], vec![1,0,0], vec![1,0,1],
        ];
        EventCodec { binder: HierBinder::new(6), paths }
    }

    pub fn encode(&self, ev: &[Sparse; 6]) -> Sparse {
        let comps: Vec<_> = self.paths.iter().cloned()
            .zip(ev.iter().cloned()).collect();
        self.binder.bind(&comps)
    }

    /// Unbind role `r` using the (possibly noisy) known others.
    pub fn query_role(&self, t: &Sparse, known: &[(usize, Sparse)], r: usize) -> Sparse {
        let mut acc = t.clone();
        for (i, atom) in known {
            acc = acc.xor(&atom.shift(self.binder.path_shift(&self.paths[*i])));
        }
        self.binder.unbind(&acc, &self.paths[r])
    }
}
