## 3. Composition Discovery Algorithm + Complexity

Discover rules R = ρ₁(src)⊕ρ₁(dst) from chained triples via **majority-threshold bundling** at N_safe=7 (my R2 committed number).

```rust
/// Discover composition rule from chains (A→B via src) ∧ (B→C via dst-pair).
/// Majority-thresholding crushes incoherent entity noise exponentially.
pub fn discover_rule(chain_residues: &[Sparse], theta: f64) -> Option<Sparse> {
    let n = chain_residues.len();
    if n < 7 { return None; } // N_safe Bonferroni floor at M=1000
    let mut freq: HashMap<u32, u32> = HashMap::new();
    for r in chain_residues {
        for &idx in &r.0 { *freq.entry(idx).or_insert(0) += 1; }
    }
    let cutoff = (theta * n as f64).ceil() as u32;
    let mut kept: Vec<u32> = freq.iter()
        .filter(|(_, &c)| c >= cutoff)
        .map(|(&i, _)| i).collect();
    kept.sort_unstable();
    if kept.is_empty() { None } else { Some(Sparse(kept)) }
}
```

